events.eventDescription: Watch the sunset with your team.
events.eventOfferings: The sun will provide you with vitamin D, an essential vitamin for your body. This is also the perfect time to take pictures for in many regions, the hour before the sun sets is called the golden hour, you will be glowing.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of you and your team with either the sunsetting behind you, or with the golden hour glow illuminating your faces.
events.eventTips: The perfect time to do this is the one hour time interval before the sunsets, predicted by your weather app.

events.eventDescription: Have a potluck dinner where everyone brings a dish to share.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each person with the food they bring.
events.eventTips: Choose something you are good at making and make enough to feed everyone in your team. If you are danger in the kitchen, buy some food.

events.eventDescription: Spoons is a fast-paced card game that is typically played with a group of 3 to 13 players. The objective of the game is to be the first player to grab a spoon from the center of the table when a specific set of conditions are met.
events.eventRules: To start the game, players sit around a table and place spoons in the center of the table, with one less spoon than the number of players. Then, a deck of cards is shuffled and dealt to each player. The objective of the game is to collect four cards of the same rank, such as four Queens or four 3s. Once the cards have been dealt, the dealer takes a card from the deck and places one of their cards face down in the center of the table. The card is then passed around the table, with each player taking a card from the deck and passing one of their cards to the player on their left. The goal is to get four of a kind as quickly as possible. Once a player has four of a kind, they grab a spoon from the center of the table. As soon as other players notice that a spoon has been taken, they must also grab a spoon as quickly as possible. The player who doesn't grab a spoon is eliminated from the game, and one spoon is removed from the center of the table. The game continues until only one player remains, and they are declared the winner. Take a picture of your initial setup, and then a picture of the winner. Also throw in a picture of the person who gets eliminated first.
events.eventTips: Focus on one number.

events.eventDescription: Watch a movie together.
events.eventOfferings: With the right movie choice, you'll be blessed with knowledge or nonsense.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of everyone snuggled up getting ready to watch the movie.
events.eventTips: Ask that one person with a subscription to a video streaming service for their credentials. Or try 123movies.

events.eventDescription: Have a karaoke night and sing your hearts out!
events.eventOfferings: Your vocal cords will be strengthened.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of someone in your team mid song singing. Get a view of the screen they are reading off of.
events.eventTips: Youtube has almost every karaoke version of a song you can think of. Connect it to a speaker to drown out the missed notes.

events.eventDescription: Go for a stroll on anything with wheels.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of you and your team mobbing on wheels. That could a inlcude a bike, rollerblades, wheelies, skateboards, unicycles, horse carriages, wagons, and or tricycles.
events.eventTips: Stay safe and wear a helmet.

events.eventDescription: Host your very own talent show.
events.eventTips: Plan this accordingly, be like ~ Yo guys, talent show next friday everyone have a talent ready to show ~ to ensure everyone is ready to showcase.

events.eventDescription: You are beautiful. Capture that beauty with a photo.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each member in your team with their own unique backdrop. Props are welcomed.
events.eventTips: Look at pinterest for inspiration.

events.eventDescription: Is luck in your favor? Test out to see if the universe if on your side with poker.
events.eventOfferings: Play for money, or play for favors ;)
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team's poker faces.
events.eventTips: All you need is a deck of cards and poker chips. If you don't have poker chips, use beans or anything that can represent value.

events.eventDescription: Create your very own 5 course menu, from the food, to the menu, to the experience.
events.eventRules: Take a photo of your 5 courses and of the menu describing those courses.
events.eventTips: A 5 course dinner menu includes an hors d'oeuvre, appetizer, salad, main course, and dessert

events.eventDescription: Jigsaw puzzles were originally called dissected maps. Thank you John Splisbury for creating the first puzzle.
events.eventRules: Take a before and after picture of your completed puzzle piece. The puzzle piece must be 250 - 500 pcs
events.eventTips: Start from the corners.

events.eventDescription: Face masks for skin care can hydrate and moisturize the skin. As well as remove excess oils, and help reduce signs of aging.
events.eventOfferings: Invest in your future. Start now in ensuring that your skin stays young and healthy as time goes on.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team with your face masks on.
events.eventTips: Get a pack of facemasks from your local store, or make your own formula.

events.eventDescription: Building is a fundamental action that makes us human. Why as children, were we so inclinded to the idea of building pillow forts.
events.eventOfferings: A sanctuary that can hold off any advisory.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your newly constructed pillow fort. Bonus if it fits everyone in your team.
events.eventTips: Gather all loose mattresses, pillows and blankets.

events.eventDescription: Legends say that fire breathes oxygen. Give life to fire, and it reward you with warmth.
events.eventOfferings: Form an intimate relationship with fire.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your bonfire night.
events.eventTips: Dead tree wood lights pretty well.

events.eventDescription: Make friendship bracelets with your team that shows how strong your team bond is.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your limbs that are wearing the bracelet in a circle.
events.eventTips: You can use anything from floss to gold, as long as it circles around your wrist and does not fall off.

events.eventDescription: 10 years from now, will you remember your teammates? You should take a moment to capture this singular moment in time that you have with your team so that 10 years from now you can all look back at this moment.
events.eventOfferings: Memories you can look back on.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team holding their single meaningful item they are going to place in the time capsule. Take a picture of the time capsule after everyone's place their item in.
events.eventTips: Place an item that means a lot to you and your team.

events.eventDescription: Our ability to create objects that can trigger senses, and share emotion is what makes us human. When was the last time you looked at a painting, and cried?
events.eventOfferings: Project your emotions into something physical.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of what each team member painted.
events.eventTips: Go to your local art shop to pick up canvases and paints if you don't have some already.

events.eventDescription: The Wright Brothers spent 4 years of research and development to create their first successful powered plane. It's going to take you at most 30 minutes.
events.eventOfferings: Harness to the power of flight.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of everyone's designed paper airplane. See whos can fly the furthest and take a picture of the winner's paper airplane.
events.eventTips: Printer paper could be useful. However, the best paper to use for a paper airplane is paper that weighs 80 - 100 grams per square meter (GSM).

events.eventDescription: Settlers of Catan is a strategy board game involving smart resource management. Your goal in Settlers of Catan is to reach ten victory points. You earn victory points from building settlements, cities, and development cards; having the longest road and the largest army.
events.eventOfferings: Glory for being the lord of Cataan.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team playing Cataan.
events.eventTips: Playing with expansion packs makes the game 100x better.

events.eventDescription: Monopoly is a real-estate board game for two to eight players. The player's goal is to remain financially solvent while forcing opponents into bankruptcy by buying and developing pieces of property. Bankruptcy results in elimination from the game. The last player remaining on the board is the winner.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team playing monopoly. Take a picture of the first person to go bankrupt. Take a picture of the winner.
events.eventTips: If you piss someone off, just tell em - That's business baby - those three words have a 95% success rate of calming anyone down.

events.eventDescription: In 1815, Mount Tambora erupted on Sumbawa, an island of modern-day Indonesia. Historians regard it as the volcano eruption with the deadliest known direct impact and secondary effects. Replicate a volcanic eruption middle school science style.
events.eventOfferings: Watch a chemical reaction unfold right in front of your eyes.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your volcano erupting.
events.eventTips: Be sure to do this experiment in a well-ventilated area and away from anything that could be damaged by the eruption

events.eventDescription: How were the pyramids built in Ancient Egypt? Why are there pyramids being discovered all around the globe? Why were ancient humans so inclinded to building pyramids? Build a human pyramid with your team.
events.eventOfferings: Open an interdimensional portal if done correctly.
events.eventRules: Stack your human bodies to form a pyramid. You must have 6 members to complete this activity. 3 people form the base, 2 the middle, 1 on top. Take a picture when it is completed.
events.eventTips: The strongest should go on the bottom.

events.eventDescription: Look out into the night sky at the infinite space that lays in front of you. It's crazy to believe that we're really just here on a floating rock moving fast through empty space. Hopefully we don't run into a black hole or anything crazy like that.
events.eventOfferings: Reassurance that you are little and a sacrificial lamb to the cosmic horrors that lay out of view and can appear at the blink of eye and you would never know and be eliminated from existence instantly.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of a constellation.
events.eventTips: Depending on the quality of your phone camera this may come out with extremely poor quality.

events.eventDescription: Share a meal with your team, it can be anything just eat in the presence of your teammates.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each teammate enjoying their meal.
events.eventTips: Bring whatever meal you are about to have to one location.

events.eventDescription: Find an orange tree and harvest its fruit if its ready.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the orange tree you're about to mug and the oranges you collect.
events.eventTips: If you don't have your own orange tree, scout your neighbors and ask if you can take theirs.

events.eventDescription: Pillow fights are often associated with childhood, but they can be enjoyed by people of all ages. It's a great way to release stress, have a good laugh, and get some exercise without taking things too seriously.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of a freeze frame of your team's faces from right before they are about to swing their pillow, and then carry on with continuing the pillow fight.
events.eventTips: Use soft pillows that won't cause any harm when hitting each other and come up with a safe word for when you can no longer take on a barrage of pillow swings, like peanut butter cookie.

events.eventDescription: Yoga is a practice that combines physical postures, breathing exercises, meditation, and relaxation techniques to promote overall health and well-being. It originated in ancient India and has been practiced for thousands of years, but has gained popularity in recent years as a form of exercise and stress relief.
events.eventOfferings: Improved flexibility and balance. Increased strength and endurance. Reduced stress and anxiety.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each team member striking any chosen yoga pose.
events.eventTips: Try an Ashtanga yoga sequence for beginners that can be found on youtube.

events.eventDescription: A wine and cheese night is a social gathering where people come together to enjoy different types of wine and cheese. Your team should provide a selection of cheeses from different regions or with varying flavors, as well as a variety of wines to pair with them. It's common to discuss the flavors and aromas of each cheese and wine, and share opinions and recommendations with each other
events.eventOfferings: Remy from Ratatouille would be so proud.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of you and your team enjoying the wine and cheese night. One person must be wearing a turtle neck.
events.eventTips: Here are some good pairings: Chardonnay and brie, Pinot Noir and Gruyere, Cabernet Sauvignon and aged cheddar, and Sauvignon Blanc and goat cheese.

events.eventDescription: Gather your team and explore the world of craft beer! Your team will sample a variety of craft beers and learn about the different brewing techniques and ingredients that give each one its unique flavor. The event will be guided by a knowledgeable host, who will provide insights and recommendations on which beers to try and how to pair them with different foods.
events.eventOfferings: Your team will get to try a variety of craft beers and learn about the different brewing techniques and flavors.
events.eventRules: Take a group photo holding your favorite beer from the tasting.
events.eventTips: Some good craft beer and food pairings include: IPA and spicy foods, porter and chocolate desserts, and wheat beer and seafood dishes.

events.eventDescription:
King's Cup is a popular drinking game that can be played with a group of friends. To play, a deck of cards is spread out face-down in a circle around a large cup or 'King's cup.' Each card in the deck is associated with a different rule or action that the players must follow.
To start the game, the first player draws a card and follows the corresponding rule. The rules for each card can vary, but some common ones include: Ace: Waterfall - The player who drew the card starts drinking and everyone else must continue drinking until the person to their right stops. Two: You - The player who drew the card chooses someone to take a drink. Three: Me - The player who drew the card takes a drink. Four: Floor - Everyone must touch the floor, and the last person to do so takes a drink. Five: Guys - All the male players take a drink. Six: Chicks - All the female players take a drink. Seven: Heaven - Everyone must raise their hands up, and the last person to do so takes a drink. Eight: Mate - The player who drew the card chooses a partner, and whenever one of them drinks, the other must too. Nine: Rhyme - The player who drew the card says a word, and everyone else must say a word that rhymes with it. The first player who can't think of a word or repeats a word takes a drink. Ten: Categories - The player who drew the card says a category, and everyone else takes turns saying something that fits the category. The first player who can't think of something or repeats something takes a drink. Jack: Make a Rule - The player who drew the card makes a rule that everyone must follow. Anyone who breaks the rule takes a drink. Queen: Question Master - The player who drew the card becomes the question master. They can ask any player a question at any time, and if that player answers instead of asking another question, they must take a drink. King: Pour - The player who drew the card pours some of their drink into the King's cup. The player who draws the fourth King card must drink the entire cup.
events.eventOfferings: Be crowned King, become a royal.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your set up, and of the person who has to drink the King's cup.
events.eventTips: Drinks can be anything from water, to soda.

events.eventDescription:
The game is played with a ping pong ball and a table with 10 cups arranged in a triangle at either end. Each team takes turns throwing the ball into the opposing team's cups. If a ball lands in a cup, the opposing team must remove the cup and drink its contents.
To start the game, the cups are filled with an equal amount of beverage. The first team takes turns throwing the ball at the other team's cups. If the ball lands in a cup, the opposing team must remove the cup and drink its contents. The cup is then placed to the side and is out of play for the rest of the game. If both team members land their balls in cups, they get to go again. If only one team member lands their ball, the other team member gets to take a shot until they miss. If both team members miss, the opposing team gets to take their turn. The game ends when a team has lost all their cups.
events.eventOfferings: Become the Michael Jordan of Pong.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the winners.
events.eventTips: Master the arc, master the game.

events.eventDescription:
Rage Cage, also known as Thunderdome or Boom Cup, is a fast-paced drinking game that is usually played with four or more players. The game is played with two ping pong balls, a table, and a set of plastic cups.
To start the game, the cups are arranged in a circle in the center of the table, and a small amount of beverage is poured into each cup. Two participants start with a cup in front of them and each hold a ping pong ball. They begin the game by trying to bounce the ping pong ball into the cup. If they make it on their first try, the participant can pass the cup to anyone in the table. If they do not make it their first try, they must pass it to the person next to them clock wise. The objective of Rage Cage is to bounce the ball into the cup, and then pass the ball and cup to the next player before they make their shot. Players continue to play in this manner, bouncing the ball into the cup and then passing it on, until someone makes a shot before the player before them has successfully passed the ball and cup to them. When this happens, stack the cup into the next person's cup, pass that stack to the following person, and the person who was stacked must pull another cup from the center and drink its contents and bounce the ball into that cup. The game continues in this manner, with players trying to stack cups as quickly as possible and forcing others to drink. The last person to be stacked on must drink the contents of the ~ loser cup ~.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your set up and the participant who was stacked last.
events.eventTips: Be on your toes and ready to pick up missed ping pong shots. This game can be played with any beverage from water to soda.

events.eventDescription:
Die is a table-based drinking game where opposing players sit or stand at opposite ends and throw a die over a certain height with the goal of either landing the die in their opponent's cup or having the die hit the table and bounce over the scoring area to the floor. The defending team attempts to catch the die one-handed after it hits the table, but before it touches a non-table surface. The game typically consists of two two-player teams with each of the four players having a designated cup on the table, but can also be played one-vs-one.
The game begins with one player from each team rolling the die, the team rolling the highest number will be able to choose either side or first toss. Players must say ~die~ before tossing to signal the impending throw. The die must travel higher than 8 feet (2.4 m) from the ground. If the opposing team disputes the height, the shot does not count. A point is awarded if the die hits the table and bounces off the defensive side of the table without being properly caught. The defending team may catch the die to nullify potential points scored. The die must be caught with one hand (juggling is permitted) but must not be trapped between any surface or body part or a point is awarded. Once the die comes in contact with the floor or stops moving, the play is dead and a point is awarded. If the die strikes the cup on a toss, the team is awarded 2 points. If the die is thrown into the opposing teams cup the throwing team is awarded 3 points and the thrower is permitted to sign the table. This game is played on a standard sheet of plywood (8 by 4 feet (2.4 by 1.2 m) of at least 12 inch (13 mm) thickness) placed on banquet tables. The game uses a standard solo cup.
events.eventOfferings: Improve your accuracy, handeye coordination, and reaction time.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the setup, and the winner.
events.eventTips: This game can be played with water as a beverage. Also feel free to look online for different variations of how the game can be played.

events.eventDescription:
There is no game more heinous than this, this is not fun, this is torture, those who play be wary you cannot trust anyone.
Have whoever is playing sit around a table. Place the glass cup on the table. The first person who starts takes both dice and rolls them on the table. The object of the game is to get a '7' and '11' or doubles of any kind. If you get a '7' an '11' or doubles, you tell someone to drink from the glass cup. The person who rolled fills the glass with however much beverage they want. The drinkee must finish the glass before the roller rolls another '7', '11', or double. If they do get the roll and the drinkee is not done, the roller gets to refill the glass and the round resets. The roller can only start rolling once the drinkee makes contact with the glass. If the roller touches the dice before the drinkee touches the glass, the roller becomes the drinkee and the drinkee becomes the roller. This can go on for a while, depending upon the luck of the roller. The game goes until people are tired of playing.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your setup and of the 'evil' person. Saves are allowed.
events.eventTips: This game can be played with water. Avoid filling to the brim if you don't want to make enemies.

events.eventDescription:
Basically like normal jenga, but more fun.
Write challenges on all of the 54 Jenga blocks. Anything from swallowing a goldfish to doing a handstand goes.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your jenga stack and some of the jenga challenges.
events.eventTips: Split up the jenga pieces amongst your team to get a wide variety of challenges.

events.eventDescription:
Paranoia is a very uncomfortable feeling, but most of the time it is something that is in your head. Even if you are suspicious that you are the subject of a conversation it is not really sociably acceptable to find out, plus you will give away that you have been eavesdropping. You also look a fool if you make a scene only to find out your paranoia was misguided!
Gather your team in a circle. The first player whispers a who question into the ear of the person on the right. For example, ~ who has the prettiest smile ~. The person asked the question says out loud the name of the person they think is the answer. That person, no matter where they are on the table, now has a decision to make. They can either find out the question that caused them to be the answer or they can play on and ask a new question. If they want to find out the question though they have to drink or rock paper scissors for the privilege. If they lose rock paper scissors, they do not find out, and the game moves on to the next who question.
events.eventOfferings: Harness your self control, or be consumed by paranoia.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the person who asked the weirded who question and was exposed.
events.eventTips: You can play this game with the rock paper scissors or drinking any beverage like water to hear the who question.

events.eventDescription:
Truth or Dare is a game that involves players taking turns to either answer a question truthfully or perform a dare chosen by the other players.
To start the game, one player will ask another player 'truth or dare?' The chosen player must then choose to either answer a question truthfully or perform a dare. If they choose truth, the other players will ask a question that the chosen player must answer honestly. If they choose dare, the other players will choose a task for the chosen player to perform.
events.eventOfferings: This is a great way to get to know each other.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of a dare that was completed that gave respect for the person who completed it.
events.eventTips: You can put a penalty for those who decide to pass on a truth or dare challenge.

events.eventDescription: Crawl around and try to find a ladybug. Once found, pick it up gently and let it crawl on your hand before releasing it back to nature.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the lady bug and of someone holding it.
events.eventTips: You can find ladybugs hiding within grass

events.eventDescription: Embrace the rain and stand outside in a light drizzle or heavy storm. Enjoy the feeling of the raindrops on your skin
events.eventRules: Take a picture of you and your team standing in the rain.
events.eventTips: Wait for a rainy day. Maybe wear a rain jacket and then immediately go back inside and change into dry clothing
events.eventOfferings: You gain a new understanding of what plants and trees go through everytime it rains.

events.eventDescription: Get low and start digging at the earth. Wiggle and find a worm.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your worm and of someone holding it
events.eventTips: They usually come out after a rainy day, you might have to dig for them.

events.eventDescription: The pen is mighter than the sword. Have each person in your team write up some of their best poems, and then recite them to each other. Set the mood with dimmed lights, candles, a stage, and turtle necks.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of someone in a turtle neck reciting their poem in front of their team.
events.eventTips: There are many types of poems one can write. For example, a haiku is consists of three lines. The first and third lines contain five syllables, while the second line contains seven syllables

events.eventDescription: Find a lemon tree and pick a lemon.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team picking a lemon, one for each member.
events.eventTips: When life gives you lemons, make lemonade.

events.eventDescription: Visit a garden or field of flowers and surround yourself with the beautiful colors and scents of nature
events.eventRules: Take a picture of a teammate surrounded by flowers.
events.eventTips: Find a rose garden, or go deep into a forest to find wild flowers. Watch out for ticks.

events.eventDescription: Take off your shoes and socks and plant your feet into the soil. Connect with the earth and feel grounded
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team barefoot in grass and or in soil.
events.eventTips: Loose soil will be easier to bury.
events.eventOfferings: Feel more connected to the natural world around you

events.eventDescription: Find some snails and race them with your friends. Use chalk to draw a racecourse and see whose snail is the fastest
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your race course, and the winner snail.
events.eventTips: You can find snails in a garden.
events.eventOfferings: Bragging rights for finding the fastest snail.

events.eventDescription: Find a succulent plant and plant it into your own pot of soil.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each teammates succulent
events.eventTips: You can safely rip off a leaf of a succulent and it will grow. Find the right soil. Don't over water they don't need too much water.
events.eventOfferings: A succulent is so low maintence.

events.eventDescription: Visit a farm or anywhere where there may be cows and leave a footprint in a fresh pile of cow poop.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the footprint, and the foot covered in cow dung.
events.eventTips: Have water or any cleaning materials close by.

events.eventDescription: Find a grassy hill and roll down it
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the nice hill you're about to roll down. Take a picture of your teammates rolling down the hill.
events.eventTips: The bigger the hill, the faster you'll go.

events.eventDescription: Get down on all fours and bear crawl around. Aren't you glad you are bipedal?
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your favorite teammates bear crawl position. The more animal like, the better.
events.eventTips: Watch a documentary on bears to learn from the masters.
events.eventOfferings: Maybe if you ever run into a grizzly bear and you start to bear crawl, it will recognize you as one of them and leave you alone.

events.eventDescription: Visit a farm or anywhere where there may be a cow and observe the gentle giant and appreciate its role in the food chain
events.eventRules: Take a picture of that beast.
events.eventTips: Mooing attracts cows to you.

events.eventDescription: Try to lure a squirrel with food or other objects. Try to get it as close as possible, but please don't destroy its trust if it does get close. Don't be that human.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the squirrel right next to you. It should be as close as possible.
events.eventTips: Don't get too close it might have rabies.
events.eventOfferings: A new best friend that does not trust you.

events.eventDescription: Spend a day at the beach.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team at the beach.
events.eventTips: Carpool to save on gas money.
events.eventOfferings: Where there is water, there is life.

events.eventDescription: Dig a hole in the sand and bury yourself up to your neck. Enjoy the feeling of the sand surrounding your body
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your teammate burried in sand.
events.eventTips: Use a shovel to make digging easier.

events.eventDescription: Use your creativity and build a sandcastle on the beach. Use shells, sticks, and other natural materials to decorate it
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your sand castle.
events.eventTips: Start from anew or find an abandoned sand castle and add onto it

events.eventDescription: Gather some wood and start a bonfire on the beach. Enjoy the warmth and the sound of the waves crashing against the shore
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your bonfire with your team around.
events.eventTips: Find a beach that allows for bonfires. Bring wood from home or from a local store.
events.eventOfferings: Fire on the beach at night hits different.

events.eventDescription: Search for sand crabs on the beach. Try to catch one and hold it gently before releasing it back to the sand. To find them, go where the waves break on the sand and when the water is receding, look for bubbles in the sand and slice through the wet sand with your hands.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of someone holding a sand crab in their hands
events.eventTips: To find them, go where the waves break on the sand and when the water is receding, look for bubbles in the sand and slice through the wet sand with your hands.
events.eventOfferings: Overcome your fear of touching weird gooy things.

events.eventDescription: This is kind of like a sand castle, except it should be able to fit 3+ people inside.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team inside your fort.
events.eventTips: If you have access to an excavator, it would make this job 100x easier.

events.eventDescription: Wrap yourself with a long strand of seaweed.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of a teammate wrapped in seaweed. They should be wrapped entirely below the neck.
events.eventTips: The waves will bring you infinite resources.
events.eventOfferings: Hopefully they make a remake of the Mummy.

events.eventDescription: Have a water balloon fight. Split up into teams, or have a free for all.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of all your water balloons before you start throwing, and take a picture of the winner.
events.eventTips: Fill your water balloos by hand, or go online and order that thing that fills 20 at a time.

events.eventDescription: Have a rap battle with your team. Either improvise or allow your teammates to have time to get ready.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each member as if they were on an album cover.
events.eventTips: Bring it back to the golden era of rap and diss your friends.

events.eventDescription: Host a wrestling tournament somewhere where theres space. Make a bracket and find out who is the strongest member in your team. Matches typically consist of 3 rounds that last for two minutes each. You can either win by a pin, which is when the person being pinned has both their scapulas on the ground for 2 seconds, or by points.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your set up, of two people wrestling in the middle of their match, and of the winner of the whole tournament.
events.eventTips: A singlet and knee sleeves are recommended.
events.eventOfferings: Find out how hard wrestling is, and connect with your opponent.

events.eventDescription: Everyone must bring an item that means a lot to them. They will present it to the rest of their team.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each person with their item.
events.eventTips: Go back to your spawn point and look for something that meant alot to you as kid.

events.eventDescription: Choose someone or some to give a makeover to. Let your makeup artist go crazy.
events.eventRules: Take a before and after picture of someone who has just had a makeover.
events.eventTips: Look on youtube for inspiration.

events.eventDescription: Get matching tattoos with your teammates.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of everyone and their matching tattoos.
events.eventTips: If your team is not up to permanently remember this moment, use those silly temporary tattoos that are put on with water.

events.eventDescription: Exchange outfits with your teammates
events.eventRules: Take a before and after picture of your team with their normal clothing, and then clothing swapped with another member in their team.
events.eventTips: Today is not a good day to wear your birthday suit.
events.eventOfferings: Put yourself in someone elses shoes.

events.eventDescription: Have a team member/s take on the one chip challenge.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your teammate inserting the chip in their mouth, chewing the chip, the bulge in their esophagus that will indicate there is a chewed up chip passing through, and of their blue tongue after they finish swallowing.
events.eventTips: Have milk nearby if you can't handle the heat.

events.eventDescription: Take out a deck of cards or multiple decks to build a card castle.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your finished castle.
events.eventTips: Understand the laws of physics to make your castle super tall.

events.eventDescription: Wet dirt, make mud balls, and throw them at each other.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your pile of mud balls, and the best mud splats.
events.eventTips: Wear white to bring out the contrast of the mud.

events.eventDescription: Shave a teammate's head bald
events.eventRules: Take a before and after picture of someone who had hair shaved bald.
events.eventTips: Donate your hair to charity.
events.eventOfferings: You gain the satisfaction of not having to style your hair.

events.eventDescription: Take turns painting your teammate's backs.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each person's back that was painted.
events.eventTips: Lay on a towel to make it easy for your painter.

events.eventDescription: Wax a patch off your hairest teammate.
events.eventRules: Take a before and after picture of the spot that was waxed.
events.eventTips: Be fast when you pull.

events.eventDescription: Take your anger out on a watermelon.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the watermelons you beat up.
events.eventTips: Don't waste the watermelon, eat it after its been broken.

events.eventDescription: Carry a member in your team on your back. Then proceed to squat them. You must break parallel on the squat for this to count as an official squat.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of someone standing straight up carrying a teammate, then a picture of them squatting breaking parrallel (side view).
events.eventTips: Breaking parallel is when your hip crease is below your knee.

events.eventDescription: Everyone bring an item they want to sell to their team. Each member has 2 minutes to persuade someone on their team to buy their item.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each person with their item.
events.eventTips: Think really hard about what the market wants
events.eventOfferings: Fate might bring an item to you that you didn't think you needed.

events.eventDescription: Pour candle wax on a teammates back.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the wax pouring on a teammates back, and then a picture of the wax on the back after its hardened.
events.eventTips: Choose someone who's into that kind of stuff I don't know man.

events.eventDescription: After a long day, anyone would go for a massage. Get a massage train going on or take turns giving each other massages.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the person who gives the best massage, and a picture of whatever limb they were using to give a massage.
events.eventTips: Baby oil or lotion will make this experience 10x better.

events.eventDescription: Find a feather that belongs to a bird.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the feather.
events.eventTips: Scout out areas where birds like to hang out.
events.eventOfferings: You now have yourself half a pen.

events.eventDescription: Make chips and guacomele with your team.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the chips and guac.
events.eventTips: An example list of ingredients includes avacados, tomatoes, serranos, onions, cilantro, lemon, garlic salt, and pepper.
events.eventOfferings: Avacados is supposed to be a super food. Become super.

events.eventDescription: Eat some pancakes with your team.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of a stack of pancakes
events.eventTips: Either make them yourself or go out to a breakfast diner.

events.eventDescription: Perform handstands with your team. Either that be against the wall or freely.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team in their handstands position.
events.eventTips: If you can't freely do a handstand, prop up against the wall to keep yourself up. Also have pillows everywhere just in case you fall over or to your side.
events.eventOfferings: A direct source of blood to your brain.

events.eventDescription: Wimhoff, an ice Shaman, has demonstrated that there are substantial health benefits to plunging your body into freezing temperatures. Embrace the uncomfortness of the cold, welcome the pain.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your teammates in a tub of water filled with ice. At least one person must have their entire body, below the neck, submerged.
events.eventTips: Do not stay longer than 5 minutes.

events.eventDescription: 10 minutes of sun exposure gives you the vitamin D your body needs for that day.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team chilling in the sun.
events.eventTips: Don't forget to apply sunscreen.

events.eventDescription: Choose a member in your team to draw a portrait of. Use a pencil and a piece of paper.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each team member with their respective portrait.
events.eventTips: Take a picture of the person you're drawing so that you can zoom in on features.

events.eventDescription: Paint a picture with anything but your hands.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the painting and the body part the painter used.
events.eventTips: Choose a body part that you want to establish a deeper connection with.

events.eventDescription: Find or buy a scarf. Everyone take turns modeling with the scarf. The scarf should be emphasized.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each member wearing a scarf.
events.eventTips: Most scarfs are typically worn around the neck.
events.eventOfferings: A new clothing item to add to your wardrobe.

events.eventDescription: There is mad respect for anyone that wears a fedora out in public. Taste that respect and model the fedora with your team.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each teammate in a fedora.
events.eventTips: Fedoras are typically worn on the head.

events.eventDescription: Bring out the fine china, its time to get caffeinated fancily. Cucumber sandwiches with the crust cut is a must.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each member sipping tea with their pinky up.
events.eventTips: Add ice to your tea if it's too hot.

events.eventDescription: Spend time reading your favorite book with your teammates. Or designate one person to read outloud to everyone.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the book you're reading.
events.eventTips: Choose a book everyone will like. You can't go wrong with the Percy Jackson series.
events.eventOfferings: Take a break from instant dopamine.

events.eventDescription: Alot can be said without having to utter a word. Strengthen your team's bond, pair up and maintain close eye contact for 1 minute. Your noses should be close to contact.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each pair making eye contact
events.eventTips: Dim the lights to increase tension.

events.eventDescription: Remember those sober middle/high school dances. Can you do it again now? Play a slow song and dance with a teammate.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of a pair slow dancing.
events.eventTips: Say Something by A Great Big World brings back so many memories

events.eventDescription: It's like poker, but rather than wagering chips and money, you wager articles of clothing
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the clothes that were removed at the end of the game
events.eventTips: Wear as many pants and shirts you can. Those are your chips.
events.eventOfferings: An elevated heart beat and some blushing

events.eventDescription: There is an iconic scene "Lifts in the River" in the movie Dirty Dancing where Johnny lifts Baby over his head. Johnny has his hands placed on Baby's hips and lifts her up over his head with her hands spread out as if shes flying. Recreate this scene.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of a pair performing this scene.
events.eventTips: If you can't do it, have other teammates help keep Baby's sub's legs up.

events.eventDescription: Split into pairs. There will be a climber, and a mountain. Have the climber start on the back of the mountain. The climber must end up in front of the mountain with their hands on the mountain's shoulders.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each pair once they have completed the task.
events.eventTips: The mountain can help in anyway, the climber just can't touch the ground.

events.eventDescription: Paint your team's nails to have matching colors.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your team's nails in a circle.
events.eventTips: Black is very neutral color.

events.eventDescription: Leave a big ol lipstick kiss print on your teammate's faces. Everyone must have one. The redder the lipstick the better.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of everyone's print.
events.eventTips: You can have multiple prints.
events.eventOfferings: An excuse to have a smooch.

events.eventDescription: Find the loosest pair of pants, and split it into pairs. Anyway possible, as a pair fit yourselves into those pants without ripping them.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each pair in their pants
events.eventTips: Sweat pants are very elastic.
events.eventOfferings: If you wanted looser pants, now you got them.

events.eventDescription: Find your biggest shirt and split into pairs. As a pair fit into that shirt.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each pair in their shirts.
events.eventTips: Easy mode, tanktop. Normal mode, short sleeve shirt. Hard mode, long sleeve shirt.

events.eventDescription: Split into pairs, give each other the nastiest wedgie humanity will never forget.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the back view of the wedgie
events.eventTips: Wear loose under garments.
events.eventOfferings: Giving birth is way more painful.

events.eventDescription: Split into pairs and just hold hands with that person. Let go once it starts to get clammy and sweaty.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each pair holding hands.
events.eventTips: Don't grip too hard you might hurt the other person's hand.
events.eventOfferings: When else would you have held this person's hand.

events.eventDescription: Did you know that you need at least 4 hugs a day for survival, 8 hugs for maintanence, and 12 hugs a day for growth? Each member must have had at least 12 hugs.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of the person who gave the best hug.
events.eventTips: Give warm up hugs to find the right squeeze to hold ratio.

events.eventDescription: Split into pairs and give each other neck hickies.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each hickey.
events.eventTips: Immediately apply ice to reduce swelling. Or apply the correct color foundation to cover it.

events.eventDescription: If you slap someones back or butt hard enough and with the correct hand placement, you can leave behind a hand print that resembles a starfish. Split into pairs and spawn starfish.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each member's starfish.
events.eventTips: Keep your palm open.

events.eventDescription: Take out a playing card. Have your team form a circle. The game starts with someone placing the card on their lips. They must exchange the card with the person sitting next to them with their lips. The person receiving must receive the card using their lips and continues down the circle. The round ends when the card falls or when the card goes around the circle.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of your circle and the card you are going to use to play the game.
events.eventTips: Find the right amount of wetness you have to make your lips to make the card stick better. But be wary, too wet will make it fall.

events.eventDescription: This is definitely something they only do in movies... But with your team, form a circle. Place a glass bottle in the middle. Each member spins the bottle. They must kiss whoever the bottle lands on. The game ends once everyone has spun the bottle.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of everyone sitting in a circle with a glass bottle in the middle.
events.eventTips: If the bottle lands in between two people, have them rock paper scissors. Winner is who the bottle chooses.

events.eventDescription: Split into pairs, or do it alone, but everyone must make a sock puppet character using their socks. They will then take turns performing for everyone. Each performance should last a minute.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each member with their designed sock puppet.
events.eventTips: Reanact a movie scene if you can't write your own script.

events.eventDescription: Have your team hit the gym altogether.
events.eventRules: Take a picture of each member doing their favorite exercise.
events.eventTips: Showcase your strength.
